news.title: Square One builds up presence in Hyderabad to target exponential growth in the city for FY 2024-25
news.para: “Hyderabad offers us the perfect canvas to put forth our creative services. There is a constant demand to outdo whatever has ever come before, and that's a challenge that we like to take up with every real estate project.” - Nishant Mehta, Director, Square One.

news.title: General Atlantic set to sell up to 5.1% stake in PNB Housing via open market on Aug 21
news.para: According to a term sheet issued by IIFL Securities, General Atlantic Singapore Fund FII Pte will sell 1.33 crore shares at a floor price of Rs 775 apiece, aiming to raise Rs 1,033 crore.

news.title: Lenders bank on SC and RBI's direction to justify JAL's admission into insolvency
news.para: Further, the lenders argued that JAL had a debt and committed default, which warrants its resolution under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (IBC).

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels Paradiso tower C declared unsafe
news.para: This is the seventh tower in the condominium of nine towers - where a vertical collapse of living rooms killed two residents in Feb 2022 - to be declared unfit.

news.title: No projects launched, Noida authority plans to reclaim 13 acres from Unitech
news.para: Officials said on Tuesday that this plot is not part of an ongoing Supreme Court case over unfinished projects of Unitech, so the Authority can cancel its allotment.

news.title: MahaRERA makes submission of quality assurance by project developers mandatory
news.para: This certificate will be based on various factors that determine the quality of the project, including the project’s structural design, stability, various tests, the types of materials used, and the skill level of the workforce involved, fire safety and fire resistance measures, etc.

news.title: NCLT affirms HDIL rights over Hyderabad property
news.para: The tribunal has held that new development agreements, after the initial joint development pact, executed by HDIL during the moratorium have violated the moratorium and adversely affected the corporate debtor's rights.

news.title: SC clears auction of Samrudhhi Realty assets to recover Rs 5,000 crore debt
news.para: However, a bench led by Justice Abhay S Oka said that if an auction of any of the assets of Essel Finance Advisors and Managers LLP is conducted, it will be subject to the final outcome of the appeal.

news.title: CCI clears Rs 4,630-crore deal between Warburg Pincus, Shriram Housing Finance
news.para: Mango Crest Investment Ltd undertakes investment holding activities. It is an affiliate of US-based Warburg Pincus. Shriram Housing Finance Ltd is a housing finance company registered with the National Housing Bank.

news.title: Building materials business expected to log significant growth: Aditya Birla Group chairman
news.para: Birla was addressing the AGM of the group's holding firm Grasim, which controls the group's flagship firms including UltraTech, Aditya Birla Finance and other investments in textiles, chemicals and paints.

news.title: Axis Ecorp targets Rs 100 crore revenue from fractional ownership in FY25
news.para: The company is planning to earn revenue of up to Rs 100 crore within the current financial year and plans to introduce three additional lots.

news.title: Welspun One acquires 22-acre land in Gurugram
news.para: The company plans to invest Rs 125 crore in the project, which is expected to create 1,500 jobs.

news.title: Flutter Entertainment invests $3.5 million to open GCC in Hyderabad
news.para: Spread over 80,000 sq ft and across three floors, the new hub will have space for over 700 employees working across data engineering, game integrity services, HR operations, procurement, safety and security and customer operations.

news.title: Sunac China warns of $2 billion half-year loss on property market downturn
news.para: China's property sector, a cornerstone of the country's economy, has been in a rough spell since 2021 as a regulatory drive on developers using excessive leverage caused a liquidity crisis.

news.title: BHIVE Workspace to add three million sq ft in next two years
news.para: BHIVE is targeting revenue of circa Rs 350 crore for FY 2024-25, effectively doubling its growth rate from previous years.

news.title: Kalpataru reports net loss of Rs 100.74 crore in FY24
news.para: Mumbai-based Kalpataru Ltd has filed the draft red herring prospectus (DRHP) to launch its IPO, which comprises a fresh issue of shares, having a face value of Rs 10 each, aggregating up to Rs 1,590 crore.

news.title: Four listed REITs distribute Rs 1,371 crore to unitholders in Q1 FY24
news.para: Indian REITs Association (IRA) data showed that in the latest June quarter, these four REITs have together distributed more than Rs 1,371 crore to over 2,45,000 unit holders.

news.title: Australia's Dexus reports annual loss of $1.5 billion in FY24
news.para: Dexus' A$14.8 billion ($9.9 billion) portfolio of offices and warehouses shrank 12.9% or A$1.9 billion in value over the year ended in June.

news.title: Rajokri residents block bulldozers, seek legal relief on demolitions from Delhi HC
news.para: Residents of Rajokri village near Vasant Kunj successfully blocked attempts by forest officials to demolish their homes. The locals, who have lived there for over three decades, have valid documents and claim the right to rehabilitation. They are now seeking a stay on demolitions from the Delhi High Court.

news.title: Goa HC dismisses appeal against demolition of illegal structures
news.para: Although the area covered by the structures could be considered small, once found to be illegal, he cannot take advantage of it, the high court observed.
